                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-472-victim2412 t18260914-472-viclabel2649"></join>, of <placeName id="t18260914-472-crimeloc2650">Leadenhall-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-472-crimeloc2650" type="placeName" value="Leadenhall-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-472-crimeloc2650" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-472-off2647 t18260914-472-crimeloc2650"></join>. On the 19th of August, about twelve o'clock, the prisoner came and looked at some ribbons; he was about an hour there, and selected about thirty pieces - I had observed him put one piece into his pocket; he said he was going to Houndsditch, and would call in half an hour; I followed him out, brought him back, and he produced two pieces, and said, "I suppose this is what you want, but it is not Mr. Tickell's;" I said I could swear to it - he was given in charge - he had paid nothing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-472-person2414">
